Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of AI and computational modeling in analogy-making, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a large corpus of raw text to automatically discover semantic relations among words suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL). The evaluation of the algorithm's performance suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of neural networks in the algorithm suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
